A change in matrix for vitamin D measurement, from plasma to serum, occured between the 2009-2011 reference periods and the 2013-2015-2017 reference periods. This change of matrix is not related to differences in values among reference periods.

A change in instrumentation and method for ferritin measurement occurred between the 2011-2013 and 2015-2017 reference periods. Uncorrected data from these methods cannot be compared. The standard operating procedures (SOPs) are available upon request.

Results corrected for the different ferritin measurement methods used for the 2011 and 2013 reference periods are presented as "Updated" characteristics. These corrected results could be compared between reference periods but note that differences in testing methods can still account for differences in the results, even in corrected data.

A change in instrumentation and method for vitamin D measurement occured between the 2009-2011-2013-2015 and the 2017 reference periods. Uncorrected data from these methods cannot be compared. The standard operating procedures (SOPs) are available upon request.
RBC folate measurements are subject to high intra-indivdual biological variation and significant analytical imprecision. The standard operating procedures (SOPs) are available upon request.

A change in instrumentation and method occured between the 2009-2011 reference periods and the 2013-2015-2017 reference periods.  Comparision of the data between reference periods should be done with caution.  RBC folate results from immunoassays cannot be compared to population based studies which used microbiological assays. The standard operating procedures (SOPs) are available upon request.
